    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Riding habits for women, in fashion from the early 18th century, used specifically for riding sidesaddle. Variously described as tailored masculinized ensembles that may include long skirts that cover riding pants, fitted jackets, top hats, and gloves.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
